<DocsLayout title="Auto-Scaling">
  <h1>Auto-Scaling</h1>
  <p>
    EncodeSwarmr's auto-scaling feature fires outbound webhook calls to your infrastructure when the job queue grows or shrinks, enabling you to dynamically provision and deprovision encoding agents. The Controller does not manage infrastructure directly — it delegates that responsibility to your existing tooling (Kubernetes, AWS ASG, custom scripts, etc.) via a simple HTTP webhook contract.
  </p>

  <h2>How Auto-Scaling Hooks Work</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>The Controller continuously monitors queue depth (absolute pending task count) and the number of connected agents.</li>
    <li>When the number of pending tasks exceeds the <code>scale_up_threshold</code> (absolute count), the Controller fires a <code>scale_up</code> webhook to your endpoint.</li>
    <li>When the number of pending tasks falls below the <code>scale_down_threshold</code> and a cooldown period has elapsed, the Controller fires a <code>scale_down</code> webhook.</li>
    <li>Your endpoint provisions or deprovisions agents and returns HTTP 200. The Controller applies a cooldown window before firing the next scale event to prevent flapping.</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>Configuration</h2>
  <p>Add the <code>autoscaling</code> block to <code>controller.yaml</code>:</p>
  <pre><code>autoscaling:
  enabled: true
  webhook_url: https://infra.example.com/hooks/encodeswarmr-scale
  secret: my-scaling-secret          # HMAC-SHA256 secret
  scale_up_threshold: 50             # pending tasks count to trigger scale-up
  scale_down_threshold: 10           # pending tasks count to trigger scale-down
  scale_up_step: 2                   # number of agents to add per scale-up event
  scale_down_step: 1                 # number of agents to remove per scale-down event
  min_agents: 1                      # never scale below this count
  max_agents: 20                     # never request above this count
  cooldown: 5m                       # minimum duration between consecutive scale events</code></pre>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Field</th><th>Type</th><th>Default</th><th>Description</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>enabled</code></td><td>bool</td><td><code>false</code></td><td>Master switch for auto-scaling</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>webhook_url</code></td><td>string</td><td>—</td><td>HTTP(S) endpoint that receives scale events</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>secret</code></td><td>string</td><td>—</td><td>HMAC-SHA256 signing secret; sent in <code>X-Signature-256</code></td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>scale_up_threshold</code></td><td>int</td><td><code>50</code></td><td>Absolute pending task count above which to scale up</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>scale_down_threshold</code></td><td>int</td><td><code>10</code></td><td>Absolute pending task count below which to scale down</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>scale_up_step</code></td><td>int</td><td><code>2</code></td><td>Number of agents to add per scale-up event</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>scale_down_step</code></td><td>int</td><td><code>1</code></td><td>Number of agents to remove per scale-down event</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>min_agents</code></td><td>int</td><td><code>1</code></td><td>Lower bound; Controller never requests fewer than this</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>max_agents</code></td><td>int</td><td><code>20</code></td><td>Upper bound; Controller never requests more than this</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>cooldown</code></td><td>duration</td><td><code>5m</code></td><td>Minimum duration between consecutive scale events</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Webhook Payload Format</h2>
  <p>All scale events are delivered as <code>POST</code> requests with a JSON body and the <code>X-Signature-256</code> HMAC header.</p>

  <h3>scale_up payload</h3>
  <pre><code>&#123;
  "action": "scale_up",
  "pending_tasks": 72,
  "active_agents": 3,
  "idle_agents": 0,
  "suggested_add": 2,
  "min_agents": 1,
  "max_agents": 20,
  "fired_at": "2025-06-01T14:32:00Z"
&#125;</code></pre>

  <h3>scale_down payload</h3>
  <pre><code>&#123;
  "action": "scale_down",
  "pending_tasks": 4,
  "active_agents": 8,
  "idle_agents": 5,
  "suggested_remove": 3,
  "min_agents": 1,
  "max_agents": 20,
  "fired_at": "2025-06-01T16:10:00Z"
&#125;</code></pre>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Field</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>action</code></td><td>string</td><td><code>scale_up</code> or <code>scale_down</code></td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>pending_tasks</code></td><td>int</td><td>Number of pending (queued) tasks at the time of firing</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>active_agents</code></td><td>int</td><td>Number of agents currently connected and processing work</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>idle_agents</code></td><td>int</td><td>Number of agents connected but not processing any task</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>suggested_add</code></td><td>int</td><td>Suggested number of agents to add (scale_up only)</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>suggested_remove</code></td><td>int</td><td>Suggested number of agents to remove (scale_down only)</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>min_agents</code></td><td>int</td><td>Configured minimum agent count</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>max_agents</code></td><td>int</td><td>Configured maximum agent count</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>fired_at</code></td><td>string</td><td>ISO 8601 UTC timestamp of the event</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <p>Your endpoint must respond with HTTP 200 within 10 seconds. Any other status code or a timeout causes the Controller to log a warning and try again after the next evaluation cycle.</p>

  <h2>UI Admin Page Walkthrough</h2>
  <p>Auto-scaling settings are managed in the admin UI under <strong>Settings → Auto-Scaling</strong>:</p>
  <ol>
    <li>Toggle <strong>Enable auto-scaling</strong> to activate the feature.</li>
    <li>Enter the <strong>Webhook URL</strong> of your scaling endpoint.</li>
    <li>Set the <strong>HMAC Secret</strong> (stored encrypted at rest).</li>
    <li>Adjust the <strong>Scale-Up Threshold</strong> and <strong>Scale-Down Threshold</strong> sliders.</li>
    <li>Set <strong>Min Agents</strong> and <strong>Max Agents</strong> bounds.</li>
    <li>Configure the <strong>Cooldown</strong> in seconds.</li>
    <li>Click <strong>Save</strong>. A test payload is fired to verify connectivity.</li>
    <li>The <strong>Scaling Events</strong> tab shows a live log of all scale_up and scale_down deliveries with response codes and timestamps.</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>Integration Examples</h2>

  <h3>Kubernetes HPA (Python webhook receiver)</h3>
  <pre><code>from flask import Flask, request, abort
from kubernetes import client, config
import json

app = Flask(__name__)
config.load_incluster_config()
apps_v1 = client.AppsV1Api()

DEPLOYMENT = "encodeswarmr-agent"
NAMESPACE   = "encoding"

@app.route("/hooks/encodeswarmr-scale", methods=["POST"])
def handle_scale():
    payload = request.get_json()
    action = payload["action"]
    suggested = payload.get("suggested_add") or payload.get("suggested_remove", 0)
    current = payload["active_agents"]
    desired = (current + suggested) if action == "scale_up" else max(1, current - suggested)
    apps_v1.patch_namespaced_deployment_scale(
        name=DEPLOYMENT,
        namespace=NAMESPACE,
        body=&#123;"spec": &#123;"replicas": desired&#125;&#125;
    )
    return "", 200</code></pre>

  <h3>AWS ASG (bash webhook receiver via AWS CLI)</h3>
  <pre><code>#!/usr/bin/env bash
# Simple example using jq + AWS CLI inside a Lambda or EC2-hosted receiver

PAYLOAD=$(cat)
ACTION=$(echo "$PAYLOAD" | jq -r '.action')
CURRENT=$(echo "$PAYLOAD" | jq -r '.active_agents')
ADD=$(echo "$PAYLOAD" | jq -r '.suggested_add // 0')
REMOVE=$(echo "$PAYLOAD" | jq -r '.suggested_remove // 0')
DESIRED=$(( ACTION == "scale_up" ? CURRENT + ADD : CURRENT - REMOVE ))
ASG_NAME="encodeswarmr-agents"

aws autoscaling set-desired-capacity \
  --auto-scaling-group-name "$ASG_NAME" \
  --desired-capacity "$DESIRED" \
  --no-honor-cooldown

echo '&#123;"status":"ok"&#125;'</code></pre>

  <h3>Custom script (bash)</h3>
  <pre><code>#!/usr/bin/env bash
# Minimal receiver that logs the event and delegates to a Nomad job

PAYLOAD=$(cat)
ACTION=$(echo "$PAYLOAD" | jq -r '.action')
ADD=$(echo "$PAYLOAD" | jq -r '.suggested_add // 0')
REMOVE=$(echo "$PAYLOAD" | jq -r '.suggested_remove // 0')

echo "$(date -u +%FT%TZ) scale action=$ACTION add=$ADD remove=$REMOVE" \
  &gt;&gt; /var/log/encodeswarmr-scaling.log

nomad job scale encodeswarmr-agent "$&#123;ADD:-$REMOVE&#125;"</code></pre>

  <h2>Cooldown Behaviour</h2>
  <p>
    After any scale event is fired, the Controller enters a cooldown period of <code>cooldown</code>. During this window:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>No further scale_up or scale_down events are emitted, regardless of queue depth changes.</li>
    <li>The current cooldown timer is shown in the <strong>Settings → Auto-Scaling</strong> UI as a countdown.</li>
    <li>The cooldown is intentionally shared between scale_up and scale_down to prevent oscillation.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Set <code>cooldown</code> to at least as long as it takes your infrastructure to provision a new agent and have it connect to the Controller; otherwise the Controller may fire multiple scale-up events before agents arrive.
  </p>

  <h2>Signature Verification</h2>
  <p>Auto-scaling webhooks use the same HMAC-SHA256 scheme as regular event webhooks. Verify the signature before trusting the payload:</p>
  <pre><code>import hmac, hashlib
from flask import request, abort

SCALING_SECRET = "my-scaling-secret"

def verify_scaling_request():
    sig_header = request.headers.get("X-Signature-256", "")
    body = request.get_data()
    expected = "sha256=" + hmac.new(
        SCALING_SECRET.encode(), body, hashlib.sha256
    ).hexdigest()
    if not hmac.compare_digest(expected, sig_header):
        abort(403, "Invalid signature")</code></pre>

